<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7903&amp;p=80503#p80503"><![CDATA[
You could replace the internal RAM with a 8K SRAM if you wanted to and had homebrew that would utilize it. It might break a game if it relies on RAM being mirrored. But you could install switches to fix this. But since it's easier to just put RAM in the cartridge that makes more sense.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Fri Jun 24, 2011 1:54 pm</p><hr />
